            I started off with thinking about the show first and foremost. A lot of the action takes place on a dark background. I wanted to match that feeling of being alone in space battling for your home by using a dark background. One of the ways I put a site together is to recycle work that's free online. For bootstrap sites, I typically use <a href="https://bootswatch.com">bootswatch</a>. This time I picked the 'Cyborg' theme. I found the bright blue primary to be a close match to the Cosmo Navy logo color. Another touch I added to the navbar was to use an anchor icon from <a href="https://fontawesome.com/icons?d=gallery">fontawesome</a>. I thought it would be a nice touch to the page since the show has a strong naval theme. Next, I then focused on trying to find pictures 
